items.body:
@editorconfig/developers editorconfig/editorconfig-vim#126 is a request to apply settings even when opening files in directories that don't exist.  How do other plugins behave when an editor is asked to open a file in a non-existent directory (for editors that support doing so)?  I think the behaviour should be both consistent across plugins and specified formally, and I don't see a clear statement in the spec.  Currently:

> When a filename is given to EditorConfig a search is performed in the directory of the given file ...

... but that doesn't clearly say whether or not the directory has to exist :) .

See also #282 .

Let's decide it before Dec 28 GMT -12 23:59....

@editorconfig/board-member
